HEADWORD: Criminology
<hw>Crim`i*nol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(-n?l"?-j?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>crimen</ets>, <ets>crimenis</ets>, crime + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A treatise on crime or the criminal
population.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The branch of sociology which studies crime and
criminals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Crim`i*nol"o*gist</wf> <pr>(-j<?/st)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

